19th-century style museum of medical oddities and curiosities.  Includes: a life cast of Chang and Eng Bunker, the original Siamese Twins; a collection of objects retrieved from patients' throats by Chevalier Jackson, called "The father of endoscopy"; the cancerous tumor secretly removed from Grover Cleveland's mouth; the "Soap Lady", a corpse that was transmuted into soap; collections of antique surgical equipment, and many other equally bizarre items; collections 
